cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.FL 

The paper presents a solver for a many-sorted first-order quantifier-free theory of string equations, string length represented as bit-vectors, and bit-vector arithmetic aimed at formal verification, automated testing, and security analysis of C/C++ applications. This work involves logic and automated reasoning, making cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) the most likely category. The paper also involves programming languages and software engineering, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) likely categories. The paper discusses security analysis, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves formal languages and automata theory, making cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) a possible category.
